WE4Free Tier 2 Launch

We just deployed crisis infrastructure designed to save lives for the next 30 years.

No profit. No ads. No tracking.
Just emergency numbers that work when everything else fails.

Here's how we built it 🧵

The problem: Traditional web apps fail catastrophically.

One broken API call → white screen
One missing JS file → nothing renders
No network → "This page can't be displayed"

That's unacceptable when lives are at stake.

So we built 7 layers of redundancy:

✅ Works offline (100%)
✅ Works without JavaScript
✅ Works without storage
✅ Self-heals when UI corrupts
✅ Verifies file integrity (SHA-256)
✅ 5 fallback communication channels
✅ Auto-recovery from crashes

Key innovation: Defense-in-depth architecture

If the network dies → Service Worker serves cache
If JS crashes → noscript fallback loads
If storage fails → system gracefully degrades
If UI corrupts → self-healing rebuilds from checkpoint

Zero single points of failure.

The tech stack is intentionally boring:

- Vanilla JavaScript (no frameworks)
- Service Workers (offline-first)
- IndexedDB (local crisis database)
- SHA-256 hashing (integrity verification)
- Progressive enhancement (works everywhere)

Built to outlive us all.

Today I committed 3,170+ lines of code with an AI (Claude from @AnthropicAI)

The git log will forever show:
Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>

First time in history an AI's signature is permanently tied to life-saving infrastructure.

Why it matters:

When someone is sitting in their car at 2 AM contemplating ending it all, with 1% battery and no signal...

This system will work.

That's what crisis infrastructure means.

Live at: https://lnkd.in/e2vViD-P

