WE4Free Tier 2 Release — Crisis‑Grade Architecture Now Live
The WE4Free Mental Health Hub has reached a major milestone with the completion and deployment of its full Tier 2 architecture. This release transforms the platform from a resilient offline‑capable site into a multi‑layer, medically‑informed crisis‑response client designed for reliability under real‑world stress conditions.
Performance Enhancements
The rendering pipeline has been optimized to reduce Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) by 500–800ms on first load. Improvements include:
• Lazy‑loading the gradient background
• Deferring geolocation and non‑critical initialization
• Using for background tasks
• Ensuring a fast solid‑color paint before visual enhancements
These changes improve first‑load performance without compromising accessibility or offline behavior.
Integrity Monitoring
A new integrity verification layer ensures that critical files remain untampered and consistent across deployments. Features include:
• SHA‑256 verification for 12 critical assets
• A live footer indicator showing system integrity status
• Four operational states: Normal, Degraded, Recovery, Emergency
• Automatic re‑checks every 60 seconds
This provides transparency and trustworthiness for users, especially in crisis contexts where reliability is essential.
Guided Emergency Escalation
A new page introduces a structured, device‑aware escalation flow modeled after medical triage patterns. The system automatically routes users through the safest available communication channel:
1. Phone call
2. SMS
3. TTY relay
4. Webchat
5. Offline emergency fallback
The interface includes progress tracking, reassurance messaging, and adaptive behavior based on device capabilities.
Self‑Healing and Sync
Tier 2 also includes:
• A self‑healing UI layer that reconstructs critical elements if they fail
• IndexedDB caching for province data and emergency numbers
• Background synchronization to keep offline data current
These systems ensure continuity even in unstable network conditions.
Deployment Summary
• Service Worker upgraded to v10
• 12 critical files deployed
• 5 HTML pages now part of the architecture
• All Tier 2 features fully operational
The platform now implements all seven architectural layers: Performance, Database, Multi‑Path Access, Integrity, Self‑Healing, Sync, and Crisis UX.
